.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This package contains named constants for all kinds of values used across
Bitcoin. It is not uncommon to have a need to use these values in code which
interacts with Bitcoin::Crypto.
.PP
Each constant can be accessed either by importing it (as shown above) or by
calling a fully qualified name, like \f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Constants::MAX_MONEY\*(C'\fR.
For backward compatibility, the second form can also be used with lowercase
name: \f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Constants::max_money\*(C'\fR.
.PP
To avoid overly long import statements, constants are organized under tags.
Unless there is a reason not to, it is recommended to import tags instead of
each constant separately. The exception is the \f(CW\*(C`:all\*(C'\fR tag, which should be
used sparingly.
.SH TAGS
.IX Header "TAGS"
.SS :all
.IX Subsection ":all"
Imports everything. Should generally be avoided to not clutter the namespace.
.SS :curve
.IX Subsection ":curve"
Contains basic secp256k1 curve data:
.PP
"CURVE_NAME", "CURVE_ORDER", "CURVE_GENERATOR"
.SS :key
.IX Subsection ":key"
Contains values which may be required when dealing with keys:
.PP
"MAX_CHILD_KEYS", "KEY_MAX_LENGTH", "WIF_COMPRESSED_BYTE"
.SS :witness
.IX Subsection ":witness"
Contains values for witness versions:
.PP
"SEGWIT_WITNESS_VERSION", "TAPROOT_WITNESS_VERSION", "MAX_WITNESS_VERSION"
.SS :bip44
.IX Subsection ":bip44"
Contains various BIP44 purpose values:
.PP
"BIP44_PURPOSE", "BIP44_COMPAT_PURPOSE", "BIP44_SEGWIT_PURPOSE", "BIP44_TAPROOT_PURPOSE"
.SS :coin
.IX Subsection ":coin"
Contains very basic coin constants:
.PP
"UNITS_PER_COIN", "MAX_MONEY"
.SS :transaction
.IX Subsection ":transaction"
Contains constants used together with transactions:
.PP
"LOCKTIME_HEIGHT_THRESHOLD", "MAX_SEQUENCE_NO", "RBF_SEQUENCE_NO_THRESHOLD", "NULL_UTXO"
.SS :sighash
.IX Subsection ":sighash"
Contains known sighash values:
.PP
"SIGHASH_DEFAULT", "SIGHASH_ALL", "SIGHASH_NONE", "SIGHASH_SINGLE", "SIGHASH_ANYONECANPAY"
.SS :script
.IX Subsection ":script"
Contains values used during script creation and execution:
.PP
"SCRIPT_MAX_STACK_ELEMENTS", "SCRIPT_MAX_ELEMENT_SIZE", "SCRIPT_MAX_OPCODES", "SCRIPT_MAX_SIZE", "SCRIPT_MAX_MULTISIG_PUBKEYS", "TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION"
.SS :psbt
.IX Subsection ":psbt"
Contains values useful for PSBTs:
.PP
"PSBT_MAGIC", "PSBT_SEPARATOR", "PSBT_GLOBAL_MAP", "PSBT_INPUT_MAP", "PSBT_OUTPUT_MAP"
.SS :bech32
.IX Subsection ":bech32"
Contains values useful for BECH32:
.PP
"BECH32", "BECH32M"
.SH CONSTANTS
.IX Header "CONSTANTS"
.SS CURVE_NAME
.IX Subsection "CURVE_NAME"
Curve name used by Bitcoin, \f(CW\*(C`secp256k1\*(C'\fR
.SS CURVE_ORDER
.IX Subsection "CURVE_ORDER"
A bytestring containing the secp256k1 curve order.
.SS CURVE_GENERATOR
.IX Subsection "CURVE_GENERATOR"
A bytestring with serialized uncompressed curve generator point for secp256k1.
.SS MAX_CHILD_KEYS
.IX Subsection "MAX_CHILD_KEYS"
Maximum number of keys which can be derived in extended key derivation. Values
above it start being recognized as hardened instead, and start counting from 0.
.SS KEY_MAX_LENGTH
.IX Subsection "KEY_MAX_LENGTH"
The maximum byte length of a serialized private key.
.SS WIF_COMPRESSED_BYTE
.IX Subsection "WIF_COMPRESSED_BYTE"
A magic byte which is used in WIFs to mark the key as compressed.
.SS SEGWIT_WITNESS_VERSION
.IX Subsection "SEGWIT_WITNESS_VERSION"
Numeric witness version used in SegWit (version 0) programs.
.SS TAPROOT_WITNESS_VERSION
.IX Subsection "TAPROOT_WITNESS_VERSION"
Numeric witness version used in Taproot (version 1) programs.
.SS MAX_WITNESS_VERSION
.IX Subsection "MAX_WITNESS_VERSION"
Numeric maximum possible witness version.
.SS BIP44_PURPOSE
.IX Subsection "BIP44_PURPOSE"
Numeric base BIP44 purpose.
.SS BIP44_COMPAT_PURPOSE
.IX Subsection "BIP44_COMPAT_PURPOSE"
Numeric BIP44 compat SegWit purpose (BIP49)
.SS BIP44_SEGWIT_PURPOSE
.IX Subsection "BIP44_SEGWIT_PURPOSE"
Numeric BIP44 native SegWit purpose (BIP84)
.SS BIP44_TAPROOT_PURPOSE
.IX Subsection "BIP44_TAPROOT_PURPOSE"
Numeric BIP44 native SegWit purpose (BIP86)
.SS UNITS_PER_COIN
.IX Subsection "UNITS_PER_COIN"
Number of satoshis that equal a single coin.
.SS MAX_MONEY
.IX Subsection "MAX_MONEY"
Number of satoshis that will ever exist.
.SS LOCKTIME_HEIGHT_THRESHOLD
.IX Subsection "LOCKTIME_HEIGHT_THRESHOLD"
First number which will be understood as timestamp in locktime checks.
.SS MAX_SEQUENCE_NO
.IX Subsection "MAX_SEQUENCE_NO"
Default and maximum possible "sequence_no" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Input.
.SS RBF_SEQUENCE_NO_THRESHOLD
.IX Subsection "RBF_SEQUENCE_NO_THRESHOLD"
Value which is used in finding out if a transaction has Replace\-By\-Fee enabled.
.SS NULL_UTXO
.IX Subsection "NULL_UTXO"
An 2\-element array reference which is an UTXO location for a coinbase transaction.
.SS SIGHASH_DEFAULT
.IX Subsection "SIGHASH_DEFAULT"
Default hashtype for digests \- only used in Taproot. Functionally equal to SIGHASH_ALL.
.SS SIGHASH_ALL
.IX Subsection "SIGHASH_ALL"
Hashtype for digesting all outputs of a transaction \- default in pre\-Taproot.
.SS SIGHASH_NONE
.IX Subsection "SIGHASH_NONE"
Hashtype for digesting no transaction outputs.
.SS SIGHASH_SINGLE
.IX Subsection "SIGHASH_SINGLE"
Hashtype for digesting only one output in a transaction, corresponding to this input.
.SS SIGHASH_ANYONECANPAY
.IX Subsection "SIGHASH_ANYONECANPAY"
Hashtype for digesting only this input and no other inputs. Cannot be used
standalone, must be binary\-or\*(Aqed with other SIGHASH constants.
.SS SCRIPT_MAX_STACK_ELEMENTS
.IX Subsection "SCRIPT_MAX_STACK_ELEMENTS"
Maximum number of elements which can be kept on a script stack and altstack
together.
.SS SCRIPT_MAX_ELEMENT_SIZE
.IX Subsection "SCRIPT_MAX_ELEMENT_SIZE"
Maximum byte size of a single stack element.
.SS SCRIPT_MAX_OPCODES
.IX Subsection "SCRIPT_MAX_OPCODES"
Maximum non\-push opcodes which can be used in a single script. Not applicable
to Taproot.
.SS SCRIPT_MAX_SIZE
.IX Subsection "SCRIPT_MAX_SIZE"
Maximum script size in bytes. Not applicable to Taproot.
.SS SCRIPT_MAX_MULTISIG_PUBKEYS
.IX Subsection "SCRIPT_MAX_MULTISIG_PUBKEYS"
Maximum OP_CHECKMULTISIG public keys.
.SS TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION
.IX Subsection "TAPSCRIPT_LEAF_VERSION"
Tree leaf version number used in Taproot tapscript spends.
.SS PSBT_MAGIC
.IX Subsection "PSBT_MAGIC"
A magic byte sequence which is required in PSBTs.
.SS PSBT_SEPARATOR
.IX Subsection "PSBT_SEPARATOR"
A byte sequence which separates PSBT maps.
.SS PSBT_GLOBAL_MAP
.IX Subsection "PSBT_GLOBAL_MAP"
A value for making use of global PSBT maps.
.SS PSBT_INPUT_MAP
.IX Subsection "PSBT_INPUT_MAP"
A value for making use of input PSBT maps.
.SS PSBT_OUTPUT_MAP
.IX Subsection "PSBT_OUTPUT_MAP"
A value for making use of output PSBT maps.
.SS BECH32
.IX Subsection "BECH32"
A value used for marking original bech32 serialization
.SS BECH32M
.IX Subsection "BECH32M"
A value used for marking bech32m serialization
.SS USE_BIGINTS
.IX Subsection "USE_BIGINTS"
Whether the module currently uses BigInts (32\-bit architecture compatibility).
Can be forced to a true value by setting \f(CW\*(C`BITCOIN_CRYPTO_USE_BIGINTS\*(C'\fR
environmental variable.
.SS ""
.IX Subsection ""
